Subject: [PATCH] Mirror konveyor.io/agentrun and konveyor.io/agent labels onto the sandbox pod

Target: konveyor/agentic-controller, PR #4 branch
        (verified against commit 1766fcb "Address PR #4 review findings")
File:   internal/controller/agentrun_controller.go (createSandbox)

Why: the controller labels the Sandbox CR (and the ACP key Secret) with
konveyor.io/agentrun, but Agent Sandbox v0.5.0 copies only
Spec.PodTemplate.ObjectMeta labels/annotations onto the pod it creates.
The pod therefore carries only agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-name-hash, and
label-based pod discovery by run name is impossible; clients must
resolve the pod by name via AgentRun.status.sandboxName. Mirroring the
labels into the PodTemplate closes that gap without changing any
behavior clients already rely on (name-based resolution keeps working).

Apply with: git apply 0001-add-agentrun-labels-to-pod-template.patch
Verified:   git apply --check passes; gofmt clean.

DO NOT send upstream without an explicit human decision (see README.md).

diff --git a/internal/controller/agentrun_controller.go b/internal/controller/agentrun_controller.go
index 2b8d4a3..599784d 100644
--- a/internal/controller/agentrun_controller.go
+++ b/internal/controller/agentrun_controller.go
@@ -338,6 +338,15 @@ func (r *AgentRunReconciler) createSandbox(
 		},
 		Spec: sandboxv1beta1.SandboxSpec{
 			PodTemplate: sandboxv1beta1.PodTemplate{
+				// Agent Sandbox v0.5.0 copies only PodTemplate metadata
+				// onto the pod, so mirror the identifying labels here to
+				// make the pod discoverable by AgentRun / Agent name.
+				ObjectMeta: sandboxv1beta1.PodMetadata{
+					Labels: map[string]string{
+						"konveyor.io/agentrun": run.Name,
+						"konveyor.io/agent":    agent.Name,
+					},
+				},
 				Spec: corev1.PodSpec{
 					Containers: []corev1.Container{
 						{
